description: Back-formation from superannuated; Latin super "over" + annus "year"

verbs.description: superannuate (third-person singular simple present superannuates, present participle superannuating, simple past and past participle superannuated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To retire or put out of use due to age.
examples: These crumbling relicks and long fired particles superannuate such expectations; bones, hairs, nails, and teeth of the dead, were the treasures of old sorcerers.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To show to be obsolete due to age.
(transitive) To give a pension to, on account of old age or other infirmity; to cause to retire from service on a pension.
